# Idea Promotion Workflow

- Capture new feature ideas in `IDEAS_BACKLOG.md` first when they are exploratory, high-level, or not implementation-ready.
- Move items to `TODO` only when they are clear enough to execute (scope, intent, and expected outcome are understandable).
- Keep `TODO` focused on actionable work; keep `IDEAS_BACKLOG.md` focused on discovery and prioritization.

# Update Rules

- If the user mentions a new concept without requesting implementation, add/update it in `IDEAS_BACKLOG.md` (and only mirror to `TODO` if explicitly requested or clearly execution-ready).
- If a feature is implemented, update `TODO` status immediately and keep wording aligned with what shipped.
- Avoid duplicate entries across sections/files unless there is a clear traceability reason.

# Practical Guardrails

- Prefer concise, de-duplicated entries grouped by area.
- Preserve existing project conventions and core-first prioritization.
